The number of confirmed COVID-19 cases in West Sussex so far as at 10 September is 70,856 (8,166.6 cases per 100,000 population). In the seven days to 05 September, there were 2,307 new confirmed cases (265.9 new cases per 100,000). In the seven days to 29 August, there were 2,207 new cases and so the new cases have risen by 5% (100 extra cases).
